part-time CET4 TEM4

ADJ If someone is a part-time worker or has a part-time job, they work for only part of each day or week. 部分时间的; 兼职的 

例： Many businesses are cutting back by employing lower-paid part-time workers. 许多商家正通过雇佣低工资的兼职工来削减开支。 

例： Part-time work is generally hard to find. 兼职工作一般很难找。 

2. ADV Part-time is also an adverb. 部分时间地; 兼职地 [ADV after v] 

例： I want to work part-time. 我想做兼职。

